post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': '[Entheogenic drugs](https://maps.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=5468), such as psychedelics, have been used throughout human history for many benefits in evolutionary growth and cognitive development.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If drugs being illegal prevented addiction, there would be no drug addicted person. Thus, there is no prevention by just keeping drugs illegal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Drugs can give individuals false perceptions of reality, inducing potentially negative behaviour.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Historically, the US government has only permitted research which [supports their agenda](https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/08/18/feds-limit-research-marijuana-medical-use/31547557/) of prohibition. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A change in the law to deny all those who suffer self inflicted physical ill-health or mental trauma, including junkies, free access to the N.H.S., would, or at least should jolt the pleasure seekers out of their surreal world in which they enjoy a ''free ride''."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Any drug with the potential of overdose can also be used as a murder weapon, especially opiates. This allows people to potentially become serial killers under less suspicion, especially in areas where access to such drugs is much less restricted. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Thousands of people [are killed](https://www.cfr.org/backgrounder/mexicos-drug-war) annually by drug cartels.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Through education, heavy advertising campaigns and controlling the packaging of tobacco, the government can make its negative effects clear despite it being legal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'An overdose of heroin is usually fatal without medical help; [during 2016](https://www.cdc.gov/drugoverdose/data/heroin.html), almost 15,500 people died from drug overdoses involving heroin in the United States.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Producers and distributors are not able to control how consumers use their products. Therefore, legalising the sale and possession of drugs necessarily would allow for this kind of abuse to increase easily despite the illegality of forcing another person to ingest them.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Other factors contribute to the opioid crisis significantly more than the legality of currently prescribed opioids. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a [correlation](https://americanaddictioncenters.org/rehab-guide/addiction-and-violence) between drug use and \\(violent\\) crime.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs deprives criminals of a substantial source of their income. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Foreign countries' dealers might find it convenient to resupply in a nearby country where drugs have been legalized, thus boosting the phenomenon of international drug trafficking, expensive to track down and halt."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "There's no reasonable way for folks to measure whether or not a drug-induced hallucinatory episode will become a violent episode any more than there's a way to determine whether someone is an angry or violent drunk. Instead the police simply deal with the drunkards after the fact rather than taking away alcohol from everyone."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If state distributed drugs freely as a prescription medicine for registered addicts, it could seriously harm the income from organized crime.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs will help treat addicts. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Heroin users](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/research-reports/heroin/what-are-medical-complications-chronic-heroin-use) experience mental disorders, such as depression, insomnia and antisocial personality disorder.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'No alcohol or tobacco company has openly killed anyone to continue selling their product.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Regulations that prohibit working under the influence of alcohol can trivially be expanded to include all drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, addicts would be forced to buy legally, meaning there is a record of their usage and authorities can intervene if there is an instance of drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Children of drug addicts would have a much higher chance of receiving the appropriate help if drug users did not have to hide.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are more effective policies than legalizing drug use to challenge drug abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Job security in an immoral industry should not be an argument for maintaining the status quo.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs have recreational and social value.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Because pain is an important clinical symptom, legal recreational opioids may delay patients from seeking care in a timely fashion.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help law enforcement agencies.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Some drugs are highly addictive; [addiction is defined as a disease](https://www.centeronaddiction.org/what-addiction/addiction-disease) by most medical associations.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In Colorado, between 2014 and 2017, [over $500 million](https://money.cnn.com/2017/07/19/news/colorado-marijuana-tax-revenue/index.html) in government revenue was raised by taxes and fees on marijuana sales. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalization improves government finances.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The black market businesses won't be able to invest in productivity-increasing \\(especially immovable\\) capital, as the threat of being caught discourages such investments. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Job security in an immoral industry should not be an argument for maintaining the status quo.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Rational discussion of the costs and benefits of smoking tobacco and negative ads led a lot of people to decide it isn't worth doing. All without prohibiting it."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Date-rape drugs are controlled presently. The current prohibition has not hindered the occurrence of date rape.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "When people overdose on illegal drugs medical staff may have a problem knowing what's in the drugs that were ingested. If drugs were legal and regulated, they could save more lives."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "That's already true in [most states \\(USA\\)](https://www.ghsa.org/state-laws/issues/drug%20impaired%20driving)"}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Research chemicals, which are used as [date rape drugs](https://drugabuse.com/date-rape-drugs/), are constantly evolving and changing formulations to escape existing regulation. It is unlikely that the law would be able to control all of them. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'During prohibition, there were very few production standards \\(if any\\), meaning the consumer did not know what \\(potentially dangerous\\) conditions the alcohol had been manufactured in \\([pg. 4](https://object.cato.org/pubs/pas/pa157.pdf)\\).'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': "This doesn't apply where there is no NHS or equivalent."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This stress would be reduced if the drugs were legal because it would remove the threat of legal danger to any concerned person.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Pharmaceutical companies might just as well synthesize new, less addictive and harmful drugs to meet the demand.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The government would be giving up authority to empower the individual. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Short-term pleasure from addictive drug consumption may lead to [irreversible impairments](https://www.health24.com/Medical/Osteoporosis/News/Graphic-This-drug-will-kill-you-within-two-years-20140709), damaging the consumer's quality of life."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Governments would be able to check what cutting agents are used within the drugs, meaning they will be safer as potentially harmful cutting agents would be banned. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It will destroy jobs for drug enforcement agencies, lawyers, judges, police, prison wardens. There is a whole industry depending on it.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'While it might be better for society if a corporation created a less addictive drug, the actual incentive would be to create the most addictive drug imaginable. The corporation would then patent this to own a monopoly and charge a huge amount for continued use.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "The ability to alter another person's mind state has potential for abuse, and utter manipulation. As a result, people will be more able to infringe on the bodily freedom/autonomy of others."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There will be less smuggling and less drug-caused conflict. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs that are currently illegal have been and are important social tools.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'A more substantial part of society will be exposed to the harmful and dangerous side effects of drugs.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Without the effect of the forbidden fruit, drugs would not be 'cool' anymore \\(subcultures, arts, musicians, writers, etc.\\). Removing this effect would minimize the number of people who use drugs because they feel insecure or want to belong in a group."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug use is not the same as drug addiction.'}
